
📘 LINUX - ARCHIVING & SSH NOTES

🔹 1. Archiving vs Compression
------------------------------
- Archiving → Combining multiple files/folders into one file
- Compression → Reducing file size

Formats:
.tar        → Archive only
.tar.gz     → Archive + compressed
.tar.bz2    → Stronger compression


🔹 2. Tar Command Basics
------------------------------
Syntax:
tar [options] archive_name files_or_folder

Options:
-c   → Create archive
-x   → Extract archive
-v   → Verbose (show files)
-f   → File name
-z   → gzip compression
-j   → bzip2 compression
-C   → Extract to directory


🔹 3. Create Archive
------------------------------
tar -cvf demo.tar demo/

Check contents:
tar -tvf demo.tar


🔹 4. Create Compressed Archive
------------------------------
tar -czvf demo.tar.gz demo/


🔹 5. Extract Archive
------------------------------
tar -xvf demo.tar


🔹 6. Extract Compressed Archive
------------------------------
tar -xzvf demo.tar.gz


🔹 7. Extract to Specific Directory
------------------------------
mkdir output
tar -xzvf demo.tar.gz -C output/


🔹 8. Backup Script (Mini Project)
------------------------------
Goal: Automatically backup folder

Script:
#!/bin/bash
tar -czvf backup_$(date +%F).tar.gz demo/

Note:
- %F gives current date in YYYY-MM-DD format

Run:
chmod +x backup.sh
./backup.sh


🔹 9. Cleanup Command
------------------------------
rm -r <folder-name>


